1
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:21,300
Celeste, I just want to ask,
how you are doing?

2
00:00:21,367 --> 00:00:25,033
You are a very successful
fashion designer now.

3
00:00:25,100 --> 00:00:26,133
I'm glad.

4
00:00:26,200 --> 00:00:27,600
You're engaged?

5
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:29,633
Ah, yes actually.

6
00:00:29,700 --> 00:00:31,167
It's beautiful, right?

7
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:32,733
I'm sorry, I have to go.

8
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,333
Because you know, I have
to go back to Manila.

9
00:00:35,433 --> 00:00:37,067
I still have a lot
of things to do.

10
00:00:37,133 --> 00:00:39,500
Wow, my God, what kind
of delivery is that?

11
00:00:39,567 --> 00:00:42,100
You don't know if it's genuine
or sarcastic.

12
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:44,400
Is he really happy to see me?

13
00:00:44,467 --> 00:00:46,700
Such trivial matters.

14
00:00:46,767 --> 00:00:47,867
Tell me the details.

15
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:48,867
Nothing, we just asked
how each other's doing.

16
00:00:48,933 --> 00:00:52,100
There's no spark?

17
00:00:52,167 --> 00:00:54,367
Nothing, what's with you?
Celeste is getting married.

18
00:00:55,633 --> 00:00:57,133
You know we have been separated
for a long time,

19
00:00:57,200 --> 00:00:58,233
she moved on already.

20
00:00:58,300 --> 00:00:59,533
I also moved on.

21
00:00:59,600 --> 00:01:02,867
No, oh my...

22
00:01:02,933 --> 00:01:06,067
Jamaica, what's this car
you got for me?

23
00:01:06,133 --> 00:01:09,600
I said vintage and not something
that conks out.

24
00:01:09,700 --> 00:01:14,067
I already scolded my contact
in the car rental services.

25
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:16,667
Just wait for my contact
who will help you there.

26
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:21,533
There you go.

27
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:23,633
AC please come to me.

28
00:01:23,700 --> 00:01:24,700
By the way, have you seen
the tarp

29
00:01:24,767 --> 00:01:27,433
in the newly built Galleon
replica chapel

30
00:01:27,500 --> 00:01:28,867
in Sitio Guibalon?

31
00:01:28,933 --> 00:01:32,333
What's with this day?

32
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:34,033
What's this?

33
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:35,400
Is this the end of the world?

34
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:37,400
Can you still handle it?

35
00:01:37,467 --> 00:01:39,300
Oh my God, my bags.

36
00:01:39,367 --> 00:01:40,433
Oh my God.

37
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:47,933
You should see that because
you're very handsome there.

38
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,633
You're not cute.

39
00:01:49,700 --> 00:01:51,233
You're not cute. You're a ugly.

40
00:01:51,300 --> 00:01:53,033
You're annoying.

41
00:01:53,100 --> 00:01:54,733
Why are you even existing?

42
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:58,133
I regret the day
that this came to me.

43
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:01,033
You are a waste of space.

44
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:04,633
I asked them to put it there
so a lot of people will see it

45
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:09,600
because that's where the very
first mass in Luzon was held.

46
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:14,267
I'm sure it will become
a tourist attraction.

47
00:02:14,367 --> 00:02:15,900
Celeste?

48
00:02:15,967 --> 00:02:17,867
Oh my God.

49
00:02:17,933 --> 00:02:18,900
This is going to be
a bit of a problem.

50
00:02:18,967 --> 00:02:20,433
A case may be filed
for what you did.

51
00:02:20,500 --> 00:02:21,600
Case right away?

52
00:02:21,667 --> 00:02:24,067
Can we invite you
to the Municipal Hall?

53
00:02:24,133 --> 00:02:25,233
Municipal Hall right away?

54
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:26,667
Could you give me a memo first?

55
00:02:26,733 --> 00:02:28,133
Yes, Miss, we have to

56
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:30,900
because we will turn you over
to the tourism office.

57
00:02:30,967 --> 00:02:32,900
You hit the galleon replica.

58
00:02:32,967 --> 00:02:35,100
Mikoy, can we invite you?

59
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:37,100
You can stand as a witness
in the Municipal Hall.

60
00:02:37,167 --> 00:02:38,633
- Okay, I'll come with you.
- Come with us.

61
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:42,767
Wait, I'll sit first.

62
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:43,800
Mister, wait.

63
00:02:43,867 --> 00:02:44,800
I'm sorry, Ma'am.
We're just doing our job.

64
00:02:45,867 --> 00:02:46,800
What do you mean job?

65
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:48,167
Wait, where will I hold?

66
00:02:48,233 --> 00:02:51,300
- What is this? Is this it?
- There's the handle, Ma'am.

67
00:02:51,367 --> 00:02:52,600
What is this?

68
00:02:52,667 --> 00:02:53,867
There's the handle, Ma'am.

69
00:02:53,933 --> 00:02:56,933
- This is the handle?
- Just hold on to that, Ma'am.

70
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,767
I'll have tetanus.

71
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,633
- Oh my God, what is this?
- She has a big problem.

72
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:02,900
Yes, she's carrying the problem
of the world.

73
00:03:02,967 --> 00:03:04,400
It's so hot!

74
00:03:23,533 --> 00:03:24,533
Yuck.

75
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,900
Haggard.

76
00:03:31,967 --> 00:03:33,867
What's this?

77
00:03:33,933 --> 00:03:35,033
There's a lot of insects.

78
00:03:36,967 --> 00:03:38,733
There's a lot of insects.

79
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:41,567
It's so itchy here.

80
00:03:41,633 --> 00:03:42,667
It's hot.

81
00:03:45,100 --> 00:03:46,067
Come on.

82
00:03:47,767 --> 00:03:49,433
Wait...

83
00:03:49,500 --> 00:03:50,667
this makes me so haggard.

84
00:03:54,167 --> 00:03:55,300
I'll help you.

85
00:03:55,367 --> 00:03:56,400
No, I'm okay.

86
00:04:04,233 --> 00:04:05,200
I'm okay.

87
00:04:16,233 --> 00:04:17,567
Hey, you blinked.

88
00:04:17,633 --> 00:04:18,933
Hey, no.

89
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,933
No. You're a cheater
and also that smile.

90
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,400
Why? What's wrong with my smile?

91
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:28,033
Hey, why are you blushing?

92
00:04:28,133 --> 00:04:30,067
You're thrilled, right?

93
00:04:30,133 --> 00:04:31,233
Of course not.

94
00:04:31,300 --> 00:04:34,467
I know what it means
if you scratch your nose.

95
00:04:34,533 --> 00:04:36,300
It means that you're lying.

96
00:04:37,933 --> 00:04:40,800
Admit that you're thrilled
Celeste, right?

97
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:42,033
No, I'm not.

98
00:04:42,100 --> 00:04:44,633
See, you scratched it again.

99
00:04:44,700 --> 00:04:46,767
You're thrilled, Celeste.

100
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:48,133
Whatever!

101
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:51,533
You lose. Hey, Celeste,
you lose!

102
00:04:51,600 --> 00:04:53,733
Hey, come back here!
You're thrilled with me.

103
00:04:53,800 --> 00:04:55,367
Celeste!

104
00:04:55,433 --> 00:04:57,333
You're a cheater!

105
00:04:57,400 --> 00:04:58,733
Hey...

106
00:04:58,800 --> 00:05:00,067
ouch.

107
00:05:00,133 --> 00:05:01,600
You're a cheater, Celeste.

108
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:04,767
You're a cheater.

109
00:05:08,133 --> 00:05:10,133
Can you please not smile like
that?

110
00:05:11,900 --> 00:05:12,900
Sorry, why?

111
00:05:12,967 --> 00:05:14,367
Just don't.

112
00:05:14,433 --> 00:05:16,367
Wait, my car and my stuff.

113
00:05:16,433 --> 00:05:18,200
Won't it get stolen?

114
00:05:18,267 --> 00:05:19,100
It's safe.

115
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:20,467
The people here are kind.

116
00:05:20,533 --> 00:05:22,133
What's with you as if
you don't know.

117
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:25,433
How would I know? I haven't been
back here for a long time.

118
00:05:25,500 --> 00:05:27,067
How easy for you to forget.

119
00:05:27,133 --> 00:05:28,300
So, what's next?

120
00:05:30,567 --> 00:05:31,567
Let's go inside.

121
00:05:33,833 --> 00:05:35,533
This is not such a good time.

122
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:40,067
Miss, you can put down
your sticks.

123
00:05:40,133 --> 00:05:41,867
You don't have
to scare me.

124
00:06:30,833 --> 00:06:33,200
Love, sorry the signal here
is weak.

125
00:06:34,900 --> 00:06:36,300
Just relax, don't panic.

126
00:06:36,367 --> 00:06:37,733
I'm going there.

127
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,733
You're saying that

128
00:06:38,800 --> 00:06:39,900
you're going to leave
your business

129
00:06:39,967 --> 00:06:42,933
that's out of town
just to be here?

130
00:06:43,033 --> 00:06:45,500
Isn't that a little
too much, Love?

131
00:06:45,567 --> 00:06:48,667
Just don't panic.

132
00:06:48,733 --> 00:06:50,400
I'll call my cousin Winston.

133
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,100
He's the best lawyer in town.

134
00:06:52,167 --> 00:06:54,433
I already asked to prepare
the chopper.

135
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:57,400
Just text me where you are,
I'll meet you there.

136
00:06:57,467 --> 00:06:58,633
I'll see you.

137
00:07:24,967 --> 00:07:28,600
Ma'am, you still
can't go to Manila

138
00:07:28,667 --> 00:07:32,200
not until the preliminary
investigation is conducted.

139
00:07:33,633 --> 00:07:35,900
That's preposterous.

140
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:37,100
I will stay here?

141
00:07:37,167 --> 00:07:38,700
I can't stay here.

142
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:40,067
I'll die.

143
00:07:40,133 --> 00:07:44,467
I'm sorry, Ma'am,
but we have to prove

144
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:45,567
that you did not do that
intentionally

145
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:47,400
or you did not intend
to destroy the property.

146
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,967
And what happened
is really an act of negligence.

147
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:52,767
Otherwise, a case may be filed
against you,

148
00:07:52,833 --> 00:07:56,300
reckless imprudence
resulting in damage to property.

149
00:07:56,367 --> 00:08:00,067
It's another case if proven that
you were using your cellphone

150
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:01,233
while driving.

151
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,200
It was an accident.

152
00:08:05,267 --> 00:08:09,467
You know, here's the thing.
So everybody will be happy,

153
00:08:09,533 --> 00:08:12,533
I'll just pay for it. Okay?

154
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,633
It only needs a little
buffing and a little paint.

155
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:21,067
Okay fine, if you don't
want me to pay the penalty

156
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:25,867
then I just have
to use connections.

157
00:08:28,667 --> 00:08:30,267
Connections?

158
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:31,300
Friends...

159
00:08:31,367 --> 00:08:33,867
I mean, I don't want
to call them

160
00:08:33,933 --> 00:08:36,333
because I don't want to trouble
them or you might also panic

161
00:08:36,400 --> 00:08:39,533
because some are generals,
judges,

162
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:43,100
top-notch lawyers, like that.

163
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:46,300
I made the dresses
of their wives.

164
00:08:46,367 --> 00:08:49,000
Celeste, you can't involve
other people here.

165
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:51,500
Can't I call a friend?

166
00:08:52,967 --> 00:08:58,867
Miss, no matter who you call,
we still have to follow the law.

167
00:08:58,967 --> 00:09:01,400
Right, Sir, Ma'am?

168
00:09:01,467 --> 00:09:02,400
That's right.

169
00:09:02,467 --> 00:09:03,500
That's right.

170
00:09:03,567 --> 00:09:06,167
You should find a good lawyer

171
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:08,833
because we will file a case
against you.

172
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:11,133
What?

173
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:32,733
No, no, oh my God.

174
00:09:32,800 --> 00:09:34,333
This can't happen to me.

175
00:09:34,400 --> 00:09:35,067
This can't happen.

176
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,867
Oh my God.

177
00:09:42,900 --> 00:09:44,167
Celeste...

178
00:09:44,233 --> 00:09:45,267
are you okay?

179
00:09:48,333 --> 00:09:49,967
Mikoy...

180
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:52,567
maybe you can talk
to your friends inside.

181
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:57,500
Tell them not to file a case
against me because honestly,

182
00:09:57,567 --> 00:09:58,800
it's such a hassle to me.

183
00:09:58,867 --> 00:10:01,933
You know, it's also
such a hassle for them.

184
00:10:02,033 --> 00:10:03,600
Yes...

185
00:10:03,667 --> 00:10:05,133
but they already
made a decision.

186
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,633
There's nothing I can do.

187
00:10:06,700 --> 00:10:09,333
You do not understand.

188
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:14,333
I can't stay long here because
I'm not from here anymore.

189
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,800
You're still from here.

190
00:10:15,867 --> 00:10:17,467
You were born here,
you grew up here.

191
00:10:19,467 --> 00:10:20,533
But this is where I got hurt

192
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:22,333
and here is where the people
who have hurt me.

193
00:10:30,633 --> 00:10:31,667
Hello, Grandma.

194
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:35,967
I'll be on my way home.

195
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:37,233
I'm just fixing some problems.

196
00:10:38,733 --> 00:10:39,733
Yes.

197
00:10:42,900 --> 00:10:44,033
Yes.

198
00:10:44,100 --> 00:10:45,200
Yes, okay.

199
00:11:32,167 --> 00:11:34,567
I said I won't come with you.

200
00:11:34,633 --> 00:11:36,900
Whether you like it or not,
we're going back to Sorsogon.

201
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:41,633
What is your problem?

202
00:11:43,300 --> 00:11:45,833
You! You are my problem.

203
00:11:45,900 --> 00:11:47,167
Me?

204
00:11:47,233 --> 00:11:48,633
So, I'm your problem?

205
00:11:50,533 --> 00:11:55,267
You are too blinded
by your ambition.

206
00:11:55,333 --> 00:11:57,767
My ambition?
Isn't this our dream?

207
00:11:57,833 --> 00:11:59,967
This is not my dream alone.

208
00:12:00,033 --> 00:12:01,133
It's just your dream.

209
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,233
This is not the life
I've dreamed of.

210
00:12:06,567 --> 00:12:07,833
Then what do you want?

211
00:12:10,333 --> 00:12:12,233
Just a simple life.

212
00:12:12,300 --> 00:12:13,433
You know, that's the problem
with you.

213
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,200
You easily get satisfied.

214
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:17,033
The problem with you
is you don't get satisfied.

215
00:12:20,767 --> 00:12:22,367
That's why you're not getting
anywhere with your life

216
00:12:22,433 --> 00:12:23,700
because of your attitude.

217
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:27,067
You know, I forced myself here
in Manila.

218
00:12:28,267 --> 00:12:30,667
I'm okay in Sorsogon.

219
00:12:30,733 --> 00:12:33,533
I did a lot of different jobs
to support you

220
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:34,533
because I love you.

221
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:37,233
But I'm already tired.

222
00:12:39,967 --> 00:12:41,933
I'm tired of rejections.

223
00:12:42,933 --> 00:12:44,167
I'm tired of all that.

224
00:12:46,467 --> 00:12:49,700
Let's go home while I still have
respect for myself.

225
00:12:51,833 --> 00:12:53,967
If you're tired,

226
00:12:54,033 --> 00:12:57,933
if you don't want it anymore,
don't involved me.

227
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:01,100
It's not my fault if I'm more
successful than you.

228
00:13:01,167 --> 00:13:03,500
You are selfish,
that's what you are.

229
00:13:03,567 --> 00:13:04,500
So it's me now.

230
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:07,367
It's me who is selfish now?

231
00:13:07,433 --> 00:13:09,067
Why?

232
00:13:09,133 --> 00:13:11,233
Is it bad to persevere in life?

233
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:12,533
Is it bad to dream?

234
00:13:16,633 --> 00:13:18,867
You are too...

235
00:13:18,933 --> 00:13:19,900
insensitive.

236
00:13:20,933 --> 00:13:23,500
Your dreams made you
insensitive.

237
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:29,533
Mikoy, I'm thankful for
everything you've done for me.

238
00:13:29,600 --> 00:13:30,567
Everything...

239
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,600
but wherever I am now...

240
00:13:35,067 --> 00:13:36,600
I worked hard for it.

241
00:13:39,900 --> 00:13:41,067
I worked hard for it.

242
00:13:42,433 --> 00:13:46,800
So don't tell me that
I'm selfish and judge me

243
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:48,100
because I'm not like that.

244
00:13:54,433 --> 00:14:04,400
This conversation
is going nowhere.

245
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:08,300
If you don't want to come
with me to Sorsogon,

246
00:14:08,367 --> 00:14:09,700
I will not force you.

247
00:14:15,067 --> 00:14:16,433
I'll just leave.

248
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:19,133
May?

249
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,933
What is this?

250
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:24,200
What happened to my cuz
is driving me crazy.

251
00:15:24,267 --> 00:15:27,033
Yes, I've been looking
for Celeste here in town.

252
00:15:27,100 --> 00:15:28,467
I've been driving around
already.

253
00:15:28,533 --> 00:15:29,700
I hope I can find her.

254
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,000
I feel sorry for her.

255
00:15:33,067 --> 00:15:37,067
Just call me
when you see her.

256
00:15:37,167 --> 00:15:38,867
Okay, I'm driving.

257
00:18:31,900 --> 00:18:34,000
No more tears, Love.

258
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:35,233
I'm here.

259
00:18:36,333 --> 00:18:38,100
Everything will be
taken cared of.

260
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:09,233
Mikoy, what?

261
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:12,067
Did you find her?

262
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:13,033
Yes.

263
00:19:13,100 --> 00:19:14,300
Damn.

264
00:19:14,367 --> 00:19:16,200
Good thing you're here.

265
00:19:16,267 --> 00:19:18,167
Is she with you?

266
00:19:18,233 --> 00:19:19,933
Can I talk to her?

267
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,700
She's not with me.

268
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:23,133
Huh?

269
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:25,167
Why is she not with you?

270
00:19:25,233 --> 00:19:26,900
Where is she?

271
00:19:26,967 --> 00:19:28,200
She's okay.

272
00:19:28,300 --> 00:19:29,733
Don't worry anymore.

273
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,033
Okay, bye.

274
00:19:31,100 --> 00:19:32,200
Thank you.

275
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:34,100
Go ahead and buy.

276
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:35,200
How much?

277
00:21:06,133 --> 00:21:08,567
Good afternoon. Welcome
to Residencia de Amor.

278
00:21:08,667 --> 00:21:09,667
This way, please.

279
00:21:22,067 --> 00:21:23,567
Welcome to Residencia de Amor.

280
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:25,533
Drinks, please.

281
00:21:25,600 --> 00:21:27,633
- Thank you.
- This way, please.

282
00:21:40,033 --> 00:21:43,000
Since there's no intention
to damage,

283
00:21:43,100 --> 00:21:45,200
I consider what you did
as a negligent act.

284
00:21:46,333 --> 00:21:49,300
The crime most applicable
to this would be...

285
00:21:49,367 --> 00:21:51,967
reckless imprudence resulting
in damage to property.

286
00:21:52,033 --> 00:21:53,100
Which is...

287
00:21:53,167 --> 00:21:55,000
probationable.

288
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:57,433
Attorney, what I want
to know is...

289
00:21:57,500 --> 00:22:00,167
am I going to jail?

290
00:22:00,233 --> 00:22:01,800
Well...

291
00:22:01,867 --> 00:22:03,533
instead of going
to jail,

292
00:22:03,600 --> 00:22:06,067
we can apply for probation,
Celeste.

293
00:22:06,133 --> 00:22:07,800
And while on probation,

294
00:22:07,867 --> 00:22:09,933
you are required
to do community service.

295
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:13,567
Which is a minimum of one month
and one day

296
00:22:13,633 --> 00:22:16,967
to a maximum of six months full
for major arrest.

297
00:22:17,067 --> 00:22:18,333
What?

298
00:22:18,400 --> 00:22:21,467
No, I can't possibly stay here.

299
00:22:21,533 --> 00:22:23,833
I have a lot of things
to attend to in Manila.

300
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:26,867
I also have a global fashion
immersion with my staff

301
00:22:26,933 --> 00:22:28,100
and with Tonito. We're leaving

302
00:22:28,167 --> 00:22:31,067
and then I have to prepare
for our wedding.

303
00:22:31,133 --> 00:22:33,167
That's impossible.

304
00:22:33,233 --> 00:22:34,633
I understand.

305
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:36,367
What is your advice, Winston?

306
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,967
To end the case...

307
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:42,000
I advise to just plead guilty.

308
00:22:42,067 --> 00:22:44,333
So there will be no long trial.

309
00:22:44,400 --> 00:22:47,600
In the meantime, while the case
is still in the fiscal,

310
00:22:47,667 --> 00:22:49,367
Celeste can go back to Manila

311
00:22:49,467 --> 00:22:51,800
and she can go back and forth
to Sorsogon.

312
00:22:51,867 --> 00:22:55,967
If the court issues a subpoena,
she needs to appear in court.

313
00:23:27,100 --> 00:23:31,133
By the way, bring the three
trays to Patricio and Adora.

314
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:32,133
To Celeste?

315
00:23:32,200 --> 00:23:33,467
Before we go back to Manila,

316
00:23:33,533 --> 00:23:35,167
can we drop by
your family's place?

317
00:23:35,233 --> 00:23:36,733
I want to meet your family.

318
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:37,733
- Father.
- Yes?

319
00:23:37,800 --> 00:23:39,067
It's Celeste.

320
00:23:39,133 --> 00:23:40,233
Celeste?

321
00:23:43,067 --> 00:23:45,933
Just one look
at her husband-to-be

322
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:49,233
he looks very impressive
and rich.

323
00:23:49,300 --> 00:23:53,900
He looks very successful
and accomplished.

324
00:23:53,967 --> 00:23:55,667
Celeste is viral.

325
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:56,767
What?

326
00:23:56,833 --> 00:23:59,167
Celeste, you are a trending
topic right now.

327
00:23:59,233 --> 00:24:03,900
Can you consider me successful,
accomplished?

328
00:24:03,967 --> 00:24:05,400
Why did you ask that?

329
00:24:05,467 --> 00:24:08,967
Our townspeople would think that
I can't fight for them

330
00:24:09,033 --> 00:24:09,967
against people from Manila.

331
00:24:10,033 --> 00:24:12,800
Technically, Celeste
is from Sorsogon

332
00:24:12,867 --> 00:24:13,967
because she grew up here.

333
00:24:14,033 --> 00:24:16,233
We are already trying to address
the situation, Vivian.

334
00:24:16,300 --> 00:24:18,067
Are you going to turn back time?

335
00:24:18,133 --> 00:24:20,833
I will be hosting an event
for our investors

336
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:23,833
and she's going to ruin it
with her stupidity.

337
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:25,433
If you didn't make me haggard

338
00:24:25,500 --> 00:24:28,600
and tell me that father had an
emergency, this and that.

339
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:31,600
I wouldn't have gone all
the way here to Sorsogon

340
00:24:31,667 --> 00:24:34,433
and I didn't end up in this mess
so technically,

341
00:24:34,500 --> 00:24:36,067
it's your fault.

342
00:24:36,133 --> 00:24:37,467
After your interview,

343
00:24:37,533 --> 00:24:40,667
the number of positive social
media engagements is growing.

344
00:24:40,733 --> 00:24:44,533
- Really?
- Celeste is here with us

345
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,833
making a sizeable donation

346
00:24:46,900 --> 00:24:48,733
to the heritage site
that she damaged.

347
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:51,600
Hmmm...

348
00:24:51,667 --> 00:24:55,200
Not to mention rendering
community service

349
00:24:55,267 --> 00:24:58,000
to make our town more beautiful.

350
00:24:58,067 --> 00:24:59,767
I can't even remember
the last time

351
00:24:59,833 --> 00:25:01,433
you said I love you...

352
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,500
to me.

353
00:25:02,600 --> 00:25:03,533
Hello, Aurelia.

354
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:06,133
Celeste, just in time
you're here.

355
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:08,167
I will introduce you to
the coordinator

356
00:25:08,233 --> 00:25:10,267
for your community service.

357
00:25:10,333 --> 00:25:12,200
You're wrong, Mayor.

358
00:25:12,267 --> 00:25:15,167
It's Celeste, not Celeste.
